en wird, dass es Gott ist, der abwesend ist.  aBlasphemy and transcendent homelessness are essential paradigms in the work of Günter Grass. However, Grass still created literature that reflected upon theology. This volume reveals the theological dimensions of Grass' literary texts, bringing literary studies and theology into dialogue through texts that, although God is absent, never forget that it is in fact God that is absent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4aBarth, Karl. 4aGrass, Günter. 4aTheologie/i.d. Literatur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aBarth, Karl.  aGrass, Günter.  atheology in literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831107147530 cprintz978311071359640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311071471540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110714715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110714715.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DKUb2021